140
00:08:14,780 --> 00:08:16,440
And the reason why, again, is geography.

141
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,840
This is Sparta. Sorry, this is Athens.

142
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,760
And Athens is in Attica.

143
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,700
And it's by the coast.

144
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:28,420
And Athens, the countryside is very hilly.

145
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,020
So it's bad for growing crops.

146
00:08:30,580 --> 00:08:32,540
But Athens has two major advantages.

147
00:08:32,900 --> 00:08:35,860
The first major advantage is
it has a very good harbor.

148
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:38,360
Okay? And also,

149
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:41,740
it's hilly.

150
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:45,620
But the hilly terrain is actually
good for growing olive trees.

151
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:51,860
Okay? Olives. It's also
very good at pottery.

152
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,340
So because of this, Athens,

153
00:08:55,520 --> 00:08:58,860
for most of its history, focused on trade.

154
00:08:59,260 --> 00:09:00,580
Right? It was a trading nation.

155
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:07,360
And because they are traders and merchants,
they are also very good at trading.

156
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:13,860
So they have a very different
culture to the Spartans.

157
00:09:13,980 --> 00:09:17,080
Okay? So the first thing is
they're very expansionist.

158
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:20,100
Okay? They're aggressive. And

159
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:24,000
the idea here is the Athens will
go and seek out new markets.

160
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:27,000
They also plant new

161
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,840
colonies throughout the Aegean.

162
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:33,120
To the west is the Aegean Sea.

163
00:09:33,260 --> 00:09:35,380
To the south is the Mediterranean.

164
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:40,940
Okay? And they will plant
colonies throughout this area.

165
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:46,460
And they have to encourage
their citizens to go out

166
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:49,080
